      <link>//crypt0.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2017-04-27/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 27 Apr 2017 18:05:01 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>//crypt0.net/daily/daily-trust-news-2017-04-27/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Daily Security news from &lt;a href=&#34;http://twitter.com/trustpath&#34;&gt;@trustpath&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;State of the Cyber Nation: UK Government Report on Cybersecurity Breaches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, it will be vital to have a documented plan in place to cope with data breaches, as organisations will be required to notify supervisory &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/state-of-the-cyber-nation-uk-government-88044/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/state-of-the-cyber-nation-uk-government-88044/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Association of Corporate Counsel Issues Guidelines for Law Firm&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JD Supra (press release) The ACC&amp;rsquo;s issuance of the guidelines follows a sharp increase in reported data breaches involving law firms, including some widely reported data &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/association-of-corporate-counsel-issues-88842/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/association-of-corporate-counsel-issues-88842/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;New self-help resources for Endpoint Protection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;called Support 101. Support 101 is designed to help you with the most &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.symantec.com/connect/forums/new-self-help-resources-endpoint-protection&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;https://www.symantec.com/connect/forums/new-self-help-resources-endpoint-protection&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Ransomware incidents surge, education a hot bed for data breaches,&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ZDNet Ransomware incidents have surged 50 percent from a year ago, educational institutions are becoming a playground for cyber espionage and 68 &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.zdnet.com/article/ransomware-incidents-surge-education-a-hot-bed-for-data-breaches-according-to-verizon/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.zdnet.com/article/ransomware-incidents-surge-education-a-hot-bed-for-data-breaches-according-to-verizon/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Cyber espionage up, but basic defences still down, DBIR shows&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cyber espionage is the most interesting aspect of the data relating to real data breaches that we are seeing because it is becoming more prevalent &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.computerweekly.com/news/450417570/Cyber-espionage-up-but-basic-defences-still-down-DBIR-shows&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.computerweekly.com/news/450417570/Cyber-espionage-up-but-basic-defences-still-down-DBIR-shows&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon 2017 Data Breach Investigations Report&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1,935 confirmed data breaches. That means you get a detailed insight into &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.verizonenterprise.com/verizon-insights-lab/dbir/2017/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.verizonenterprise.com/verizon-insights-lab/dbir/2017/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;1.1 Billion Identities Leaked Via Data Breaches in 2016; Email Is The&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trak.in (blog) In total, there were 1209 data breaches across the world, which resulted in the exposure of these 1.1 billion identities. Interestingly, while the number &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://trak.in/tags/business/2017/04/27/1-1b-identities-leaked-data-breach-email/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://trak.in/tags/business/2017/04/27/1-1b-identities-leaked-data-breach-email/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;How can CIOs best secure the future of their company data?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip; warnings from cyber security experts, who expressed their concern that come 2017, businesses will be subject to a significant rise in data breaches, &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.thecsuite.co.uk/cio/security-cio/how-can-cios-best-secure-the-future-of-their-company-data/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.thecsuite.co.uk/cio/security-cio/how-can-cios-best-secure-the-future-of-their-company-data/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Hackers plead guilty to 2015 TalkTalk data breach&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Despite this victory, data breaches are constantly happening, and the threat is gaining momentum. A recent example of a significant breach was the &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cbronline.com/news/cybersecurity/business/hackers-plead-guilty-2015-talktalk-data-breach/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.cbronline.com/news/cybersecurity/business/hackers-plead-guilty-2015-talktalk-data-breach/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;1.1 bn identities exposed in data breaches in 2016: Symantec&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New Delhi, Apr 26 (PTI) Nearly 1.1 billion identities were exposed by cyber criminals in data breaches across the globe last year, almost double &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/1.1-bn-identities-exposed-in-data-breaches-in-2016-symantec/1/939112.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/1.1-bn-identities-exposed-in-data-breaches-in-2016-symantec/1/939112.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;P2PE&amp;rsquo;s Silver Lining In Cybercrime&amp;rsquo;s Dark Cloud&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data breaches are not exactly news  since the Target breach of 2013, they&amp;rsquo;ve gone from being something that was little considered outside a fairly &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.pymnts.com/news/security-and-risk/2017/finding-the-p2pe-silver-lining-in-the-dark-cloud-of-expanding-cybercrime-bluefin-technology/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.pymnts.com/news/security-and-risk/2017/finding-the-p2pe-silver-lining-in-the-dark-cloud-of-expanding-cybercrime-bluefin-technology/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Thales: 34% of U.S. Federal Government Agencies Experienced Data Breach in&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yahoo Finance When it comes to data breaches, 34 percent of federal respondents experienced a data breach in the last year and 65 percent experienced a data &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://finance.yahoo.com/news/thales-34-u-federal-government-120000601.html&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://finance.yahoo.com/news/thales-34-u-federal-government-120000601.html&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s Just Plain Risky Not to Do A Risk Analysis: Recent OCR Settlement One&lt;/h3&gt;
